com.example.atheneum.models

Annotation Type Transaction.Type


  • @Retention(value=SOURCE)
public static @interface Transaction.Type
    Creates new annotation type that checks the value of an integer to see if it is equal to either CHECKOUT or RETURN. CHECKOUT and RETURN constants used to simulate an enum. An actual enum class is not necessary since enums use more memory than integer constants and we only have two values that we care about.

    See: https://android.jlelse.eu/android-performance-avoid-using-enum-on-android-326be0794dc3 https://stackoverflow.com/a/21874183/11039833
